turns.speaker: M
turns.content: What time is it?  They're supposed to run around midnight.

turns.content: This is great, isn't it?  Look at the night we've got here, couldn't be better.

turns.content: How could we forget to bring it?  I hope the moon stays out.

turns.content: You cold?  Do you want my jacket?  Oh, we should've brought the blanket.  Our blanket.

turns.content: This is great, isn't it?  A six pack would be just the ticket right now.

turns.content: I can't believe I forgot.  I'm like a kid.  It's amazing I got out of the house with my fly zipped.

turns.content: You think they can hear us talk?  Or feel the vibrations in the sand when we move around?

turns.content: Think about the people in Kansas, they had to get plane tickets and hotel reservations to see this.  We live forty minutes away.  It's too good to pass up.

turns.content: Ah, Augie.

turns.content: Oh man, this is great, isn't it?  I wouldn't miss this for anything.  Here, think about this, all right, I know you're not interested, but think about this.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Somewhere out there, this huge mass of silver fish swimming this way.

turns.content: They don't know why, we don't know why.  Nobody sent them an invitation or a map, it wasn't a decision, just-

turns.content: all as one, this time release instinctual little firecracker went off and they all turned and formed a line as long as the California coast and started swimming.  And they're swimming right now as if that's all that matters.

turns.content: They just turn as one and start the swim that brings them right here to where we stand, for a massive celebration of sex and death.
